{
  "stem": "14387.2",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "They said it had never happened before that they'd held the train up to waiting for two hours.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "Now, let me tell you something.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "You may think that we were very important people.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "We were not.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "We were just very ordinary people.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And the Norwegian government did this for us because they knew we wanted to get out, and they made all these arrangements.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we got on the train in Moscow and we traveled across Moscow for seven days.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We were in third-class compartments, so other people in the compartments-- I had a-- oh yes, my baby was born in Stockholm, so I had a six-months-old baby with me.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I fed him, I breastfed him.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And that's about all-- he was six months old, but that's about all the nourishment we had except that we-- when the train stopped at stations, we could always get a little food.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Like they had apples which I would-- I'd taken along a little scraper and scraped the apples and mashed some eggs.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I had a little box like a little lunch box and I washed it in that.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And diapers, yes.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We had taken along-- friends in Stockholm had torn up all their sheets and when we told them what we planned to do, they said, well, how are you going to manage with diapers?",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They tore up sheets and towels and things, and I had all these diapers which I could discard along the way because those days, you didn't have disposable diapers.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And so that's how we managed.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And we'd have seven days on the train and we got to Vladivostok.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "In Vladivostok, there were many, many hundreds of refugees coming from all over Europe, and some of them didn't have any place to go from there.",
      "word_count": 26
    }
  ],
